<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 2:58PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Carroll
and northwestern Heard Counties through 330 PM EDT...
At 258 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Tyus, or 10 miles
southwest of Carrollton. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Carrollton, Bowdon, Ephesus, Roopville, Tyus and Blackjack Mountain.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
